The United States has expressed deep concern over the escalating violence in Yemen and the resulting deaths of civilians. They specifically mentioned the attacks that killed an ambulance driver, a journalist, and civilians in different parts of the country. The US is calling on all sides of the conflict to avoid harming civilians and comply with international humanitarian law. They also emphasize the importance of ensuring the safety and freedom of movement for humanitarian personnel in Yemen. The US is particularly concerned about the violence in Taiz and the need for unimpeded assistance to reach all Yemenis in need. They are urging all parties to cooperate with the United Nations in reaching a cease-fire and resuming peace talks to find a lasting solution to the crisis in Yemen.